WEBVTT

1
00:00:39.304 --> 00:00:44.435
Look, her first high-end retail shopping experience.

2
00:00:44.509 --> 00:00:46.306
Her nanny tried to take her to Baby Gap...

3
00:00:46.377 --> 00:00:48.538
but she'd just cry and cry.

4
00:00:48.613 --> 00:00:51.104
She was a professional shopper at age three.

5
00:00:51.182 --> 00:00:52.444
Oh, wow!

6
00:00:52.517 --> 00:00:54.610
Remember when she was on the cover of "Seventeen"?

7
00:00:54.686 --> 00:00:57.211
She had so much potential back then.

8
00:00:57.288 --> 00:01:00.416
Look at her. She could have been a Playmate by now.

9
00:01:00.492 --> 00:01:03.052
Hello! She's a lawyer.

10
00:01:03.128 --> 00:01:05.619
-That's way better. -Why?

11
00:01:05.697 --> 00:01:07.062
There she is!

12
00:01:07.132 --> 00:01:09.623
You always said she has the perfect shaped head...

13
00:01:09.701 --> 00:01:12.568
for a tiara!

14
00:01:12.637 --> 00:01:15.629
Look at that slime dog!

15
00:01:15.707 --> 00:01:19.404
It was so nice of you to make this for Elle's wedding shower.

16
00:01:19.477 --> 00:01:21.911
I can't scrapbook worth a damn.

17
00:01:21.980 --> 00:01:24.414
I took a class on it at community college.

18
00:01:24.482 --> 00:01:26.211
-She got a "B." -Plus!

19
00:01:28.586 --> 00:01:30.554
The day she passed her LSAT!

20
00:01:30.622 --> 00:01:32.954
I swallowed some of that Silly String.

21
00:01:33.024 --> 00:01:34.355
It wouldn't be the first time.

22
00:01:34.425 --> 00:01:37.952
Look at that. Her first day at Harvard.

23
00:01:38.029 --> 00:01:39.929
Unbelievable. Awesome.

24
00:01:39.998 --> 00:01:43.365
The Bend and Snap!

25
00:01:43.434 --> 00:01:46.164
I love that. I did it last night naked.

26
00:01:46.237 --> 00:01:49.764
-You did not. -Yes. I busted a window.

27
00:01:49.841 --> 00:01:53.538
Oh, my God, there's Bruiser's first highlights.

28
00:01:53.611 --> 00:01:56.136
Is this the key to her first office at the firm?

29
00:01:56.214 --> 00:02:00.651
Remember that Caribbean decor? It was genius.

30
00:02:00.718 --> 00:02:05.314
Look, there she is with Congresswoman Rudd...

31
00:02:05.390 --> 00:02:08.291
when they started the Harvard alumni women's event.

32
00:02:08.359 --> 00:02:10.953
-Yeah. -That's two kick-ass women.

33
00:02:11.029 --> 00:02:14.123
I like them. I really like them.

34
00:02:15.533 --> 00:02:18.832
The first day they met! Emmett loves her already.

35
00:02:18.903 --> 00:02:20.996
You can see it in his eyes.

36
00:02:21.072 --> 00:02:22.198
Emmett and Elle.

37
00:02:22.273 --> 00:02:26.334
They're truly Romeo and Juliet without the dying.

38
00:02:26.411 --> 00:02:27.708
Paulette?

39
00:02:27.779 --> 00:02:29.974
Oh, my God! Girls, I think it's her.

40
00:02:30.048 --> 00:02:32.482
-Quick! Lights out! -OK!

41
00:02:35.853 --> 00:02:38.014
Paulette?

42
00:02:38.089 --> 00:02:41.525
I thought we were supposed to be at the movies by 9:00.

43
00:02:41.593 --> 00:02:44.562
Surprise!

44
00:02:51.102 --> 00:02:52.899
We got her!

45
00:02:52.971 --> 00:02:55.303
Oh, my God! Margot, Serena, I cannot believe...

46
00:02:55.373 --> 00:02:57.034
you guys flew all the way here!

47
00:02:57.108 --> 00:02:59.508
-No biggie. -On the contrary.

48
00:02:59.577 --> 00:03:01.511
It's a huge biggie. Thank you.

49
00:03:01.579 --> 00:03:03.342
You guys are the best.

50
00:03:03.414 --> 00:03:07.544
Speaking of biggies, can we see your ring again?

51
00:03:07.619 --> 00:03:10.952
Not your Delta Nu ring, Elle.

52
00:03:11.022 --> 00:03:13.684
You mean, this one?

53
00:03:15.893 --> 00:03:19.226
Clarity between F.L. and V.V.S. Nice girdle diameter.

54
00:03:19.297 --> 00:03:21.731
Cut impeccable. It's a keeper.

55
00:03:21.799 --> 00:03:24.029
Thanks!

56
00:03:24.102 --> 00:03:26.969
Oh, my gosh, it's from Emmett!

57
00:03:27.038 --> 00:03:30.235
That's me and Emmett on Fenway baseball field.

58
00:03:30.308 --> 00:03:31.969
It's his favorite place in the whole world.

59
00:03:32.043 --> 00:03:35.171
I love snow globes.

60
00:03:36.314 --> 00:03:38.612
I can hear the ocean.

61
00:03:38.683 --> 00:03:41.618
Listen, honey, you're a full-time bride now...

62
00:03:41.686 --> 00:03:43.483
so you'll need a whole new wardrobe.

63
00:03:43.554 --> 00:03:46.785
I'm not quitting my job, you guys.

64
00:03:46.858 --> 00:03:48.917
Do you guys remember that feeling we used to get...

65
00:03:48.993 --> 00:03:51.120
during a really intense Spinning class?

66
00:03:51.195 --> 00:03:55.393
That we feel so truly amazing about ourselves?

67
00:03:55.466 --> 00:03:58.162
That's how I feel being a lawyer. I love it.

68
00:03:58.236 --> 00:04:01.228
I have this huge annual review coming up...

69
00:04:01.306 --> 00:04:03.501
so keep 'em crossed, girls.

70
00:04:03.574 --> 00:04:05.098
Crossed!

71
00:04:07.145 --> 00:04:09.306
Congratulations, you did it.

72
00:04:09.380 --> 00:04:13.339
With three wrong answers, you've managed to undermine...

73
00:04:13.418 --> 00:04:17.684
the entire foundation upon which our legal system's built.

74
00:04:17.755 --> 00:04:21.122
And by the way...

75
00:04:21.192 --> 00:04:23.717
it only took me two wrong answers.

76
00:04:31.369 --> 00:04:35.931
Sweetie, you customized my ring? Again?

77
00:04:36.007 --> 00:04:38.771
Emmett, you are never going to believe my news!

78
00:04:38.843 --> 00:04:40.970
-What? -Fenway Park!

79
00:04:41.045 --> 00:04:44.037
You, me, two rings, and one recently ordained umpire...

80
00:04:44.115 --> 00:04:45.343
right on the entry field!

81
00:04:45.416 --> 00:04:47.441
Infield. What are you talking about?

82
00:04:47.518 --> 00:04:49.816
It turns out the starting pitcher for the Red Sox...

83
00:04:49.887 --> 00:04:52.014
has an unfortunate unibrow problem.

84
00:04:52.090 --> 00:04:54.149
He goes to Nadia, my waxer...

85
00:04:54.225 --> 00:04:56.056
so the team pulled some strings with the site manager...

86
00:04:56.127 --> 00:04:57.788
and we're getting married at Fenway!

87
00:04:57.862 --> 00:05:00.353
Are you serious?

88
00:05:00.431 --> 00:05:03.662
Are you sure this is what you want to do?

89
00:05:03.735 --> 00:05:07.398
I can married anywhere and it wouldn't matter.

90
00:05:07.472 --> 00:05:09.303
That's a lie.

91
00:05:09.374 --> 00:05:14.073
I'm getting married under the Green Monster!

92
00:05:14.145 --> 00:05:16.136
Yes!

93
00:05:16.214 --> 00:05:18.182
And in just three months and four days!

94
00:05:18.249 --> 00:05:20.513
Emmett, we have so much to talk about.

95
00:05:20.585 --> 00:05:23.554
I want everybody who matters to us to be there.

96
00:05:25.490 --> 00:05:28.254
Oh, my God! I almost forgot!

97
00:05:29.994 --> 00:05:30.928
You want me to what?

98
00:05:30.928 --> 00:05:32.259
You want me to what?

99
00:05:32.330 --> 00:05:34.890
A biological birth parent search.

100
00:05:34.966 --> 00:05:36.831
For your dog.

101
00:05:36.901 --> 00:05:40.268
For my Chihuahua-American Bruiser Woods.

102
00:05:40.338 --> 00:05:43.933
I found him abandoned years ago.

103
00:05:44.008 --> 00:05:47.739
Miss, I'm the highest-paid, most sought after...

104
00:05:47.812 --> 00:05:50.872
private investigator in the greater Boston area.

105
00:05:50.948 --> 00:05:52.575
That's precisely why we came to you, Detective.

106
00:05:52.650 --> 00:05:56.347
It is absolutely vital that we find Bruiser's mother pronto.

107
00:05:56.421 --> 00:06:00.687
His father might be more difficult. You know dogs.

108
00:06:00.758 --> 00:06:02.123
May I ask why?

109
00:06:02.193 --> 00:06:04.127
Of course. "Martha Stewart Weddings"...

110
00:06:04.195 --> 00:06:07.062
recommends a 4 to 6-week window for RSVPs...

111
00:06:07.131 --> 00:06:09.656
and I can't send the invitation without an address.

112
00:06:09.734 --> 00:06:13.101
And the sooner I get started on the calligraphy the better.

113
00:06:13.171 --> 00:06:16.106
You want to send an invitation to your wedding...

114
00:06:16.174 --> 00:06:18.734
to your dog's mother. And you're serious?

115
00:06:18.810 --> 00:06:20.141
Detective, if I have to make room...

116
00:06:20.211 --> 00:06:22.145
for my second cousin's vegan diet coach...

117
00:06:22.213 --> 00:06:23.942
you better believe I'll make room for the mother...

118
00:06:24.015 --> 00:06:26.711
of the one loving creature who's always been there for me.

119
00:06:26.784 --> 00:06:29.912
In fact, I can't believe I haven't done this sooner!

120
00:06:29.987 --> 00:06:32.751
I'm thinking the same thing.

121
00:06:39.964 --> 00:06:41.795
-Elle! -Hi, Mr. Blaine.

122
00:06:41.866 --> 00:06:44.130
-The client is thrilled. -Good!

123
00:06:44.202 --> 00:06:46.602
How you seamlessly negotiated that deal?

124
00:06:46.671 --> 00:06:50.107
-lt was simply magnifique. -Thank you.

125
00:06:50.174 --> 00:06:51.402
Big staff meeting today, kiddo.

126
00:06:51.476 --> 00:06:55.037
All right. I got my fingers crossed.

127
00:06:55.112 --> 00:06:57.546
Milton, two shots, extra foam.

128
00:06:57.615 --> 00:07:00.277
-Wow. Thanks, E.W. -No problem!

129
00:07:00.351 --> 00:07:02.615
-Go get 'em today. -Thanks.

130
00:07:02.687 --> 00:07:04.655
Soy for you, honey. No dairy.

131
00:07:04.722 --> 00:07:06.553
That's right. Thank you. Your call list is endless.

132
00:07:06.624 --> 00:07:08.592
-lt is? -We better get right on it.

133
00:07:10.127 --> 00:07:12.618
Kevin, you shouldn't have!

134
00:07:12.697 --> 00:07:15.165
I'm not sure they're giving me the promotion today.

135
00:07:15.233 --> 00:07:17.167
It's just a widespread yet credible rumor.

136
00:07:17.235 --> 00:07:19.760
It's from me and the girls.

137
00:07:19.837 --> 00:07:21.532
Oh, right!

138
00:07:23.674 --> 00:07:25.198
Now do me.

139
00:07:28.579 --> 00:07:30.843
I feel like the luckiest girl in the world.

140
00:07:30.915 --> 00:07:32.644
-Me, too! -You do?

141
00:07:32.717 --> 00:07:34.776
I had no idea I could be this happy...

142
00:07:34.852 --> 00:07:37.719
without accruing credit card debt.

143
00:07:37.788 --> 00:07:39.551
Already?

144
00:07:39.624 --> 00:07:42.991
Well, Miss Woods, even the weird ones get cracked.

145
00:07:43.060 --> 00:07:45.824
-You ready? -Yes!

146
00:07:48.132 --> 00:07:50.726
Bruiser Woods...

147
00:07:50.801 --> 00:07:53.326
meet your mom.

148
00:07:53.404 --> 00:07:56.202
Bruiser...your cheekbones.

149
00:07:58.142 --> 00:07:59.575
And it's all in there.

150
00:07:59.644 --> 00:08:02.112
Good luck finding whatever it is you're looking for.

151
00:08:03.848 --> 00:08:07.306
Oh, my God! She's a Bostonian!

152
00:08:09.954 --> 00:08:13.082
Bruiser, we're here!

153
00:08:13.157 --> 00:08:14.988
As your adoptive mother, I'm sure you're nervous...

154
00:08:15.059 --> 00:08:16.492
about meeting your birth mother...

155
00:08:16.561 --> 00:08:21.123
but hear her out, OK? I'm sure she had her reasons.

156
00:08:21.198 --> 00:08:23.598
Bruiser, your mother lives at...

157
00:08:23.668 --> 00:08:25.397
the top secret Versace think-tank!

158
00:08:25.469 --> 00:08:27.528
I told you they had one!

159
00:08:27.605 --> 00:08:28.731
No, ma'am.

160
00:08:28.806 --> 00:08:31.036
Unless you have a pass, you cannot go up there.

161
00:08:31.108 --> 00:08:33.042
Lucky I always keep it on me.

162
00:08:33.110 --> 00:08:36.511
Hold on. It's right here.

163
00:08:36.581 --> 00:08:38.242
There you go.

164
00:08:38.316 --> 00:08:40.375
What is it?

165
00:08:40.451 --> 00:08:42.078
It's my double platinum V.V.I.P. Versace...

166
00:08:42.153 --> 00:08:44.212
Preferred Customer identification card.

167
00:08:44.288 --> 00:08:47.519
Available only to those that've shopped on five continents.

168
00:08:47.592 --> 00:08:49.423
If that fails to satisfy you, you can also contact...

169
00:08:49.493 --> 00:08:52.053
Billy Dailey, head of customer relations.

170
00:08:52.129 --> 00:08:53.460
You got the wrong VERSACE, lady.

171
00:08:53.531 --> 00:08:55.692
Really? Donatella's not here?

172
00:08:55.766 --> 00:08:57.063
Bruiser, where are you going?

173
00:08:57.134 --> 00:08:59.227
Bruiser!

174
00:08:59.303 --> 00:09:00.600
Ma'am!

175
00:09:03.441 --> 00:09:04.635
Bruiser?

176
00:09:04.709 --> 00:09:07.177
Get back here!

177
00:09:07.244 --> 00:09:09.303
Where are you going?

178
00:09:11.682 --> 00:09:15.243
Bruiser, I didn't know you were so athletic.

179
00:09:20.725 --> 00:09:23.694
What is it?

180
00:09:28.833 --> 00:09:30.130
Oh, my God!

181
00:09:34.238 --> 00:09:37.139
You, come here!

182
00:09:37.208 --> 00:09:40.302
Come on! Open this door immediately!

183
00:09:40.378 --> 00:09:41.572
What are you doing here?

184
00:09:41.646 --> 00:09:46.345
You have my dog's mom, and I need her right now!

185
00:09:46.417 --> 00:09:48.442
Absolutely not. I'm not authorized to release...

186
00:09:48.519 --> 00:09:50.487
any subjects from their containment units.

187
00:09:50.554 --> 00:09:53.455
I'm not even allowed to have a key.

188
00:09:53.524 --> 00:09:55.549
Swallow the thing one time, and all of a sudden...

189
00:09:55.626 --> 00:09:58.527
you're the weird key swallower who can't be trusted.

190
00:09:59.997 --> 00:10:02.591
I don't think you're understanding me.

191
00:10:02.667 --> 00:10:04.134
I'm willing to pay for her.

192
00:10:04.201 --> 00:10:05.793
These animals aren't for sale, ma'am.

193
00:10:05.870 --> 00:10:07.599
They're the legal property of this facility.

194
00:10:07.672 --> 00:10:10.971
What kind of facility is this?

195
00:10:14.311 --> 00:10:16.108
Mr. Livermore, I'm so sorry!

196
00:10:16.180 --> 00:10:19.581
Elle, this VERSACE is a cosmetic testing facility.

197
00:10:19.650 --> 00:10:22.813
-Oh, no! -Bruiser's mom's a test subject.

198
00:10:22.887 --> 00:10:24.718
I want her out of there immediately.

199
00:10:24.789 --> 00:10:26.814
Animal test subjects can only be surrendered...

200
00:10:26.891 --> 00:10:29.223
on a voluntary basis, and they're not volunteering.

201
00:10:29.293 --> 00:10:31.818
After I get through with them, they'll be begging.

202
00:10:31.896 --> 00:10:33.329
And I'm not just taking Bruiser's mom.

203
00:10:33.397 --> 00:10:36.366
I'll bust all those dogs out of that doggie dungeon.

204
00:10:36.434 --> 00:10:38.766
"Research Science and Critter Exploitation"?

205
00:10:38.836 --> 00:10:41.999
This VERSACE's owned by the C'est Magnifique Corporation!

206
00:10:42.073 --> 00:10:43.700
That's fantastic!

207
00:10:43.774 --> 00:10:46.174
Our law firm represents C'est Magnifique.

208
00:10:46.243 --> 00:10:47.870
We can tell them to fix this.

209
00:10:47.945 --> 00:10:50.470
I can't wait to take this to the partners.

210
00:10:50.548 --> 00:10:53.642
But how are you going to convince them?

211
00:10:53.718 --> 00:10:55.686
Presenting...

212
00:10:58.823 --> 00:11:02.919
Abandoned at birth, I was on my own at an early age...

213
00:11:02.993 --> 00:11:07.862
fighting for survival on the streets of Beverly Hills...

214
00:11:07.932 --> 00:11:11.333
making his way down the boulevard of broken dreams,

215
00:11:11.402 --> 00:11:14.735
turning tricks at Hollywood and Vine...

216
00:11:14.805 --> 00:11:17.137
yet even when I found a loving mother...

217
00:11:17.208 --> 00:11:20.609
I couldn't shake this nagging emptiness in my heart.

218
00:11:20.678 --> 00:11:23.306
It was like a void. When I looked in the mirror...

219
00:11:23.380 --> 00:11:25.371
who was it that was looking back at me?

220
00:11:25.449 --> 00:11:27.940
This is Bruiser's question.

221
00:11:28.018 --> 00:11:32.045
And in a way, aren't we all Bruisers?

222
00:11:32.123 --> 00:11:35.388
I think yes. Thank you.

223
00:11:37.795 --> 00:11:40.525
Ms. Woods, this is a law firm...

224
00:11:40.598 --> 00:11:43.396
not an animal rights advocacy group.

225
00:11:43.467 --> 00:11:45.901
We're lawyers. We have to fight for justice.

226
00:11:45.970 --> 00:11:47.904
And this is definitely unjust.

227
00:11:47.972 --> 00:11:51.738
In this case, the cost of beauty is way too high.

228
00:11:51.809 --> 00:11:54.175
I can't believe I said that, but it's true.

229
00:11:54.245 --> 00:11:56.304
What we fight for...

230
00:11:56.380 --> 00:11:58.678
is our clients and their best interests.

231
00:11:58.749 --> 00:12:02.446
But isn't doing the right thing in everybody's best interest?

232
00:12:02.520 --> 00:12:05.512
I think you're confusing the right thing and the law.

233
00:12:05.589 --> 00:12:09.252
You didn't think they were the same, did you?

234
00:12:09.326 --> 00:12:12.386
Why don't we get back to business...

235
00:12:12.463 --> 00:12:14.954
and discuss your very bright future?

236
00:12:15.032 --> 00:12:17.023
Pardon me, I don't mean to interrupt...

237
00:12:17.101 --> 00:12:20.502
but I just-- What you're saying is...

238
00:12:20.571 --> 00:12:23.199
if C'est Magnifique follows the letter of the law...

239
00:12:23.274 --> 00:12:26.710
even if it ends up hurting living beings...

240
00:12:26.777 --> 00:12:30.975
we're just doing our job?

241
00:12:31.048 --> 00:12:34.779
I'm sorry, Mr. Blaine...

242
00:12:34.852 --> 00:12:38.185
I don't think I can work with people who believe that.

243
00:12:40.558 --> 00:12:44.358
You know what? You're right.

244
00:12:44.428 --> 00:12:46.692
Thank you, Mr. Blaine.

245
00:12:46.764 --> 00:12:48.959
You shouldn't have to work with people who believe that.

246
00:12:49.033 --> 00:12:51.092
Absolutely. I knew you would understand.

247
00:12:51.168 --> 00:12:53.432
You're fired, Elle.

248
00:12:53.504 --> 00:12:54.994
What?

249
00:12:55.072 --> 00:12:58.838
We only have room for serious lawyers here.

250
00:12:58.909 --> 00:13:02.777
Take the rest of the day to clear out your things.

251
00:13:02.847 --> 00:13:06.840
But the secretarial pool already gave me a balloon.

252
00:13:06.917 --> 00:13:09.408
Keep the balloon, if you wish.

253
00:13:19.997 --> 00:13:22.465
Please, Emmett, just go away.

254
00:13:22.533 --> 00:13:24.831
Why don't you come on out, sweetie?

255
00:13:24.902 --> 00:13:26.995
I know Bruiser doesn't blame you.

256
00:13:27.071 --> 00:13:29.938
But I'm all he has to speak for him in this world...

257
00:13:30.007 --> 00:13:31.474
and I have completely failed him.

258
00:13:31.542 --> 00:13:35.535
You know what I thought the first time I saw you?

259
00:13:35.613 --> 00:13:39.014
"God, that woman wears a lot of pink"?

260
00:13:39.083 --> 00:13:43.281
No. I thought...

261
00:13:43.354 --> 00:13:45.948
"That woman is really special."

262
00:13:46.023 --> 00:13:50.357
"She believes she can make a difference and she will."

263
00:13:50.427 --> 00:13:55.262
So...come on out and let's talk about it.

264
00:13:55.332 --> 00:13:57.357
No.

265
00:13:57.434 --> 00:14:01.234
We could go over some wedding details.

266
00:14:04.108 --> 00:14:06.542
How about that? It revolves.

267
00:14:06.610 --> 00:14:07.907
And it illuminates.

268
00:14:07.978 --> 00:14:10.310
It's even got the Red Sox colors.

269
00:14:10.381 --> 00:14:12.781
That's fantastic, honey!

270
00:14:12.850 --> 00:14:15.011
Speaking of red socks...

271
00:14:15.085 --> 00:14:16.950
you're not getting cold feet, are you?

272
00:14:17.021 --> 00:14:18.249
About what?

273
00:14:18.322 --> 00:14:20.950
How's it going to look? A Harvard law professor...

274
00:14:21.025 --> 00:14:23.493
married to a lawyer who got fired from her first job.

275
00:14:23.560 --> 00:14:25.551
Fired for something she believes in.

276
00:14:25.629 --> 00:14:27.187
It's going to look like...

277
00:14:27.264 --> 00:14:32.395
"There goes the luckiest guy in the whole world."

278
00:14:33.504 --> 00:14:35.529
Thanks.

279
00:14:43.314 --> 00:14:46.306
Holy crap!

280
00:14:46.383 --> 00:14:50.444
It's gorgeous!

281
00:14:50.521 --> 00:14:52.546
The material keeps falling apart.

282
00:14:52.623 --> 00:14:54.147
No!

283
00:14:54.224 --> 00:14:56.419
Amy, is something wrong?

284
00:14:58.629 --> 00:15:01.154
You can't do a scallop trim on the outer hoop skirt.

285
00:15:01.231 --> 00:15:04.064
The material's too delicate. It'll just fall apart.

286
00:15:04.134 --> 00:15:06.364
But in two out of three home tests it held.

287
00:15:06.437 --> 00:15:08.428
I am so sorry, Elle.

288
00:15:12.876 --> 00:15:15.401
No biggie. I guess I don't need...

289
00:15:15.479 --> 00:15:18.346
a scallop trim on the outer hoop skirt.

290
00:15:18.415 --> 00:15:20.508
I'll be fine.

291
00:15:20.584 --> 00:15:22.518
What is it that you said back when I couldn't...

292
00:15:22.586 --> 00:15:26.420
fit into my white spandex pantsuit for my wedding?

293
00:15:26.490 --> 00:15:28.014
If the fabric doesn't work with you...

294
00:15:28.092 --> 00:15:29.821
don't work with it.

295
00:15:29.893 --> 00:15:31.053
It's one of my favorite mantras.

296
00:15:31.128 --> 00:15:34.529
That is so true, and I know the most perfect organza!

297
00:15:34.598 --> 00:15:37.533
Or something really classy like...

298
00:15:37.601 --> 00:15:40.126
Iike white leather!

299
00:15:40.204 --> 00:15:43.367
I'll call the guy that did my car seats.

300
00:15:43.440 --> 00:15:46.841
Wait...that's it.

301
00:15:46.910 --> 00:15:51.313
Don't fight the fabric. Change it.

302
00:15:51.382 --> 00:15:54.215
OK, but white leather?

303
00:15:55.786 --> 00:15:59.119
If the law is what's keeping Bruiser's mother locked up...

304
00:15:59.189 --> 00:16:01.487
I shouldn't be fighting it, I should be changing it.

305
00:16:01.558 --> 00:16:04.459
Everybody, I'm going to make...

306
00:16:04.528 --> 00:16:06.860
animal testing for cosmetics illegal!

307
00:16:06.930 --> 00:16:10.696
I know that making a dog wear mascara and blush is wrong...

308
00:16:10.768 --> 00:16:12.633
This isn't just about Bruiser's mom anymore...

309
00:16:12.703 --> 00:16:14.261
this is about the fact that every day...

310
00:16:14.338 --> 00:16:16.636
that I put on my Gold Goddess luminescent blush...

311
00:16:16.707 --> 00:16:19.904
some poor little innocent animal might be suffering for it.

312
00:16:19.977 --> 00:16:22.104
You don't realize how horrible something is...

313
00:16:22.179 --> 00:16:23.806
until it happens to you personally.

314
00:16:23.881 --> 00:16:25.678
Like breastfeeding.

315
00:16:25.749 --> 00:16:28.479
And if I want to give a voice to Bruiser...

316
00:16:28.552 --> 00:16:30.884
I have to go to the place that gave a voice to the people!

317
00:16:30.954 --> 00:16:35.857
Oh, my God! The headquarters of "Cosmopolitan" magazine!

318
00:16:37.461 --> 00:16:40.157
Better! Ladies...

319
00:16:40.230 --> 00:16:42.289
I'm going to Washington!

320
00:16:43.700 --> 00:16:44.826
D.C., here I come!

321
00:16:44.902 --> 00:16:47.370
If anybody can handle this, it's you, honey.

322
00:16:47.438 --> 00:16:50.965
I got a call from the Delta Nu 24-hour housing hotline.

323
00:16:51.041 --> 00:16:52.406
Your apartment's all set.

324
00:16:52.476 --> 00:16:54.808
-Great! -Elle!

325
00:16:56.313 --> 00:17:01.410
Oh, my God! You look like the Fourth of July!

326
00:17:01.485 --> 00:17:04.921
Makes me want a hot dog real bad.

327
00:17:04.988 --> 00:17:08.424
Yeah, OK. You got to get going, honey.

328
00:17:08.492 --> 00:17:09.652
OK.

329
00:17:11.195 --> 00:17:13.129
-Elle, look at this. -What's that?

330
00:17:13.197 --> 00:17:15.165
According to "Animal Fair" magazine...

331
00:17:15.232 --> 00:17:18.099
your new boss is the best groomed woman in Washington.

332
00:17:18.168 --> 00:17:20.568
Her beagle's name is Dolly Madison...

333
00:17:20.637 --> 00:17:24.073
which is my grandma's stripper name.

334
00:17:24.141 --> 00:17:25.904
Isn't that a good sign?

335
00:17:25.976 --> 00:17:27.671
Oh, my gosh. A job with a brilliant congresswoman...

336
00:17:27.744 --> 00:17:29.075
who's also a fellow Harvard alum.

337
00:17:29.146 --> 00:17:32.309
You'll do great, Elle. It's destiny.

338
00:17:32.382 --> 00:17:34.509
But isn't planning the wedding of the century...

339
00:17:34.585 --> 00:17:37.679
and changing the law kind of hard?

340
00:17:37.754 --> 00:17:40.348
Paulette, I taught Bruiser how to shop online.

341
00:17:40.424 --> 00:17:43.393
I think I can handle Congress.

342
00:17:43.460 --> 00:17:45.860
See ya.

343
00:18:23.934 --> 00:18:26.300
Home sweet home. You ready?

344
00:18:26.370 --> 00:18:27.769
OK.

345
00:18:27.838 --> 00:18:29.271
Welcome to the Wellington, ma'am.

346
00:18:29.339 --> 00:18:31.398
It's a thrill to be here!

347
00:18:50.494 --> 00:18:52.485
Time to legislate!

348
00:18:54.698 --> 00:18:56.165
No.

349
00:19:00.037 --> 00:19:02.028
Too Nancy.

350
00:19:02.105 --> 00:19:04.369
Too Hillary.

351
00:19:04.441 --> 00:19:07.239
Too Monica.

352
00:19:07.311 --> 00:19:10.075
Too perfect for words!

353
00:19:15.852 --> 00:19:17.717
Hi!

354
00:19:17.788 --> 00:19:20.552
Good morning, fellow public servants.

355
00:19:20.624 --> 00:19:22.387
It's my first day.

356
00:19:26.930 --> 00:19:28.090
Nice briefcase.

357
00:19:28.165 --> 00:19:30.690
Huh? Thank you.

358
00:19:33.203 --> 00:19:34.864
Hi!

359
00:19:39.509 --> 00:19:43.707
Last item on our agenda--Elle Woods.

360
00:19:43.780 --> 00:19:45.805
Personal Rudd hire, taking up a bill...

361
00:19:45.882 --> 00:19:48.612
on animal testing in the cosmetic industry.

362
00:19:48.685 --> 00:19:50.414
I'm sorry, Rudd's backing that?

363
00:19:50.487 --> 00:19:51.977
Matter of conscience, whatever.

364
00:19:52.055 --> 00:19:54.785
Who knows? Maybe it'll boost our female demographic.

365
00:19:54.858 --> 00:19:56.758
The point is we're animal lovers now.

366
00:19:56.827 --> 00:20:00.661
If this is so important to Rudd, shouldn't I be handling it?

367
00:20:00.731 --> 00:20:03.564
No, Timothy, not when we have a woman...

368
00:20:03.634 --> 00:20:05.568
who according to Rudd, is one of the shrewdest...

369
00:20:05.636 --> 00:20:07.831
Iegal and political minds of our time.

370
00:20:09.973 --> 00:20:13.306
Hello, patriots!

371
00:20:13.377 --> 00:20:14.844
I don't think I've been this excited...

372
00:20:14.911 --> 00:20:17.106
since Gucci became a publicly traded company.

373
00:20:17.180 --> 00:20:20.741
Oh, my God, it's Capitol Barbie.

374
00:20:20.817 --> 00:20:22.944
She's so shiny.

375
00:20:23.020 --> 00:20:24.920
So where should I start?

376
00:20:24.988 --> 00:20:26.455
Excuse me, sweetie?

377
00:20:26.523 --> 00:20:30.118
Intern orientation is down the hall in Room 216.

378
00:20:30.193 --> 00:20:33.924
That's before 217 and after 215.

379
00:20:33.997 --> 00:20:36.295
Oh, my God! That is so sweet of you!

380
00:20:36.366 --> 00:20:38.163
You think I'm an intern?

381
00:20:38.235 --> 00:20:41.170
That anti-wrinkle all-salmon diet really works.

382
00:20:41.238 --> 00:20:42.432
Who are you?

383
00:20:42.506 --> 00:20:47.068
-I'm sorry-- -Elle Woods, welcome!

384
00:20:47.144 --> 00:20:49.704
I haven't seen you since the alumni meeting!

385
00:20:49.780 --> 00:20:53.011
-I know! How are you? -Good!

386
00:20:53.083 --> 00:20:55.074
This is Elle Woods, everyone.

387
00:20:55.152 --> 00:20:58.417
Basically me when I first came to D.C...

388
00:20:58.488 --> 00:21:01.582
so make her feel at home.

389
00:21:01.658 --> 00:21:03.216
You ready to hit the ground running?

390
00:21:03.293 --> 00:21:05.318
Are these not my comfortable heels?

391
00:21:05.395 --> 00:21:09.456
-Cute shoes. -Thank you. They are comfy.

392
00:21:10.801 --> 00:21:13.292
Here's Bruiser. Welcome.

393
00:21:14.771 --> 00:21:17.968
Oh, you little sugar!

394
00:21:18.041 --> 00:21:19.770
Back her up, people.

395
00:21:19.843 --> 00:21:22.710
This is the most collaborative bunch on the Hill...

396
00:21:22.779 --> 00:21:24.406
So gather them together...

397
00:21:24.481 --> 00:21:26.449
talk strategy as soon as you get settled in.

398
00:21:26.516 --> 00:21:28.074
-And, Elle? -Yes?

399
00:21:28.151 --> 00:21:31.177
-Welcome to Washington. -Thank you!

400
00:21:31.254 --> 00:21:34.189
Okey-dokey.

401
00:21:34.257 --> 00:21:37.158
I missed the part about where my office is.

402
00:21:37.227 --> 00:21:40.060
The desk. Right here.

403
00:21:43.367 --> 00:21:46.768
All righty. Then I'm going to need a glue gun...

404
00:21:46.837 --> 00:21:50.933
some pinking shears, and five yards of grosgrain ribbon.

405
00:21:51.007 --> 00:21:52.998
Yeah, that'll do it.

406
00:21:56.113 --> 00:21:58.445
Well, look at you.

407
00:21:58.515 --> 00:22:00.506
You can run your wedding coordinator business...

408
00:22:00.584 --> 00:22:02.415
during all that legislative downtime.

409
00:22:02.486 --> 00:22:03.976
Don't be silly, Grace.

410
00:22:04.054 --> 00:22:06.284
This is to plan my own wedding to Emmett.

411
00:22:06.356 --> 00:22:09.018
See, this is us. He had this made for me.

412
00:22:09.092 --> 00:22:12.255
That's him, and that's me smiling.

413
00:22:12.329 --> 00:22:13.694
Maybe he'll make one of you and me.

414
00:22:13.764 --> 00:22:15.527
You'll be talking and I'll be throwing up.

415
00:22:15.599 --> 00:22:18.067
Speaking of nuptials, wait till I tell...

416
00:22:18.135 --> 00:22:19.796
the congresswoman that I was invited...

417
00:22:19.870 --> 00:22:21.804
to John McCain's nephew's wedding.

418
00:22:21.872 --> 00:22:23.737
He's really quite a sweet kid.

419
00:22:23.807 --> 00:22:25.399
Tell me something, Timothy...

420
00:22:25.475 --> 00:22:28.035
is it difficult for you to breathe with...

421
00:22:28.111 --> 00:22:30.272
your mouth flat against your employer's butt?

422
00:22:30.347 --> 00:22:32.975
I don't know, Grace. Is it difficult to see...

423
00:22:33.049 --> 00:22:35.108
with your head in the Minority Whip's lap?

424
00:22:35.185 --> 00:22:37.415
It was the distinguished gentlemen from lowa.

425
00:22:37.487 --> 00:22:40.149
His wife had recently left him and we just talked.

426
00:22:40.223 --> 00:22:43.192
Right. Because if you did "visit" his district...

427
00:22:43.260 --> 00:22:45.694
you should've gotten some legislation out of it.

428
00:22:45.762 --> 00:22:46.888
How would you even know...

429
00:22:46.963 --> 00:22:49.431
when you're busy chasing interns on a skateboard?

430
00:22:49.499 --> 00:22:52.366
Excuse me? Who wants to talk animal testing?

431
00:22:52.436 --> 00:22:54.802
Write a bill, Britney. I don't have a car!

432
00:23:00.777 --> 00:23:02.176
Snap Cup time

433
00:23:02.245 --> 00:23:04.543
Gather ye round

434
00:23:04.614 --> 00:23:07.412
Friends and foes together

435
00:23:07.484 --> 00:23:09.918
United and bound

436
00:23:09.986 --> 00:23:12.318
Pass it to your neighbor

437
00:23:12.389 --> 00:23:14.516
Instead of blowing up

438
00:23:14.591 --> 00:23:16.821
And we'll find harmony and love

439
00:23:16.893 --> 00:23:19.157
In the Snap Cup!

440
00:23:20.664 --> 00:23:23.098
Don't tell me you don't know what a Snap Cup is?

441
00:23:25.001 --> 00:23:26.935
OK, I'll explain it.

442
00:23:27.003 --> 00:23:30.234
You are going to write down an anonymous praise note...

443
00:23:30.307 --> 00:23:32.241
on a little warm fuzzy.

444
00:23:32.309 --> 00:23:33.469
Warm fuzzy?

445
00:23:33.543 --> 00:23:34.976
Yes. Compliments about your co-workers.

446
00:23:35.045 --> 00:23:36.307
Just something nice.

447
00:23:36.379 --> 00:23:39.746
Then you deposit them in the sacred vessel.

448
00:23:39.816 --> 00:23:43.274
The Snap Cup is essential to any bipartisan environment.

449
00:23:43.353 --> 00:23:45.218
Consider 1998 Spring Carnival.

450
00:23:45.288 --> 00:23:48.314
The Delta Nus partnered with the Kappa Kappa Gammas...

451
00:23:48.391 --> 00:23:51.258
on Project Kissing Booth. Big problems.

452
00:23:51.328 --> 00:23:52.522
Go ahead, write.

453
00:23:52.596 --> 00:23:54.826
So, a whole heated debate transpired...

454
00:23:54.898 --> 00:23:56.957
over the whole tongue-no tongue policy.

455
00:23:57.033 --> 00:23:58.864
I think you know what side the Kappas were on.

456
00:23:58.935 --> 00:24:01.870
Anyway, it really helped us move past the conflict...

457
00:24:01.938 --> 00:24:03.428
and I think it can help us today.

458
00:24:03.507 --> 00:24:06.874
Let's just try this, OK?

459
00:24:06.943 --> 00:24:09.275
Thank you, Reena. Thank you.

460
00:24:09.346 --> 00:24:10.540
Thanks for that.

461
00:24:10.614 --> 00:24:12.707
Thank you, Timothy.

462
00:24:14.084 --> 00:24:20.353
So now, the Snap Cup mistress--me--recites.

463
00:24:21.391 --> 00:24:23.188
Good, I got mine.

464
00:24:24.528 --> 00:24:27.827
"Grace always has the confidence to speak her mind.

465
00:24:27.898 --> 00:24:30.958
"Plus, she looks terrific in charcoal."

466
00:24:31.034 --> 00:24:33.434
And, voila, snaps for Grace!

467
00:24:33.503 --> 00:24:36.472
You see? Our first Snap Cup!

468
00:24:36.540 --> 00:24:40.442
This is so exciting! I wonder what'll happen next?

469
00:24:40.510 --> 00:24:43.479
All right, this is...

470
00:24:43.547 --> 00:24:48.007
"What do Elle Woods and the Snap Cup have in common?"

471
00:24:48.084 --> 00:24:50.314
A riddle. That's so cool.

472
00:24:50.387 --> 00:24:51.911
I love riddles.

473
00:24:51.988 --> 00:24:54.821
"They're both..."

474
00:24:58.061 --> 00:25:00.120
"stupid."

475
00:25:00.196 --> 00:25:01.925
Enough already.

476
00:25:01.998 --> 00:25:04.796
Maybe we can do something actually worthwhile...

477
00:25:04.868 --> 00:25:06.301
Iike attend the hearing of the committee...

478
00:25:06.369 --> 00:25:08.633
you need to crack. I'll take you myself.

479
00:25:08.705 --> 00:25:12.664
Thank you, Grace. That's very generous of you.

480
00:25:12.742 --> 00:25:16.112
See, I think the Snap Cup really works.

481
00:25:19.249 --> 00:25:20.409
Wow.

482
00:25:20.483 --> 00:25:22.747
Good morning.

483
00:25:22.819 --> 00:25:25.913
This is just like on C-SPAN except I'm not bored.

484
00:25:25.989 --> 00:25:27.320
You're in the wrong room, sweetheart.

485
00:25:27.390 --> 00:25:29.290
Intern orientation is in room...

486
00:25:29.359 --> 00:25:32.556
216? Yes, I've heard. Thank you.

487
00:25:37.100 --> 00:25:40.263
Hi, I'm Elle Woods. I'm not an intern.

488
00:25:40.337 --> 00:25:41.827
Rob Cole. Me, neither.

489
00:25:41.905 --> 00:25:44.430
I'm the new legislative aide to Congresswoman Rudd.

490
00:25:44.507 --> 00:25:46.532
I'm an old congressman from Delaware.

491
00:25:46.610 --> 00:25:50.102
I've been to Delaware! No sales tax. Good one, sir.

492
00:25:51.147 --> 00:25:53.547
Committee is called to order.

493
00:25:55.485 --> 00:25:59.444
Welcome to the special meeting of the...

494
00:25:59.522 --> 00:26:00.989
Excuse me. Sorry.

495
00:26:01.057 --> 00:26:03.719
Committee of Energy and Commerce.

496
00:26:03.793 --> 00:26:07.627
Before we turn to our official agenda...

497
00:26:07.697 --> 00:26:09.790
are there any introductory remarks?

498
00:26:09.866 --> 00:26:11.527
Madam chairwoman...

499
00:26:11.601 --> 00:26:13.432
Grace Rossiter, chief of staff...

500
00:26:13.503 --> 00:26:15.300
Representative Rudd, Massachusetts.

501
00:26:15.372 --> 00:26:17.135
As our newest legislative assistant...

502
00:26:17.207 --> 00:26:20.870
will be spearheading a campaign under your committee...

503
00:26:20.944 --> 00:26:22.673
I'm sure she'd love the floor.

504
00:26:22.746 --> 00:26:27.012
Thus I yield to my colleague, the lady in hot pink.

505
00:26:27.083 --> 00:26:29.677
You have the floor, lady in hot pink.

506
00:26:29.753 --> 00:26:31.220
Me?

507
00:26:31.287 --> 00:26:35.155
Would you care to more specifically identify yourself?

508
00:26:35.225 --> 00:26:36.817
Oh, sure!

509
00:26:36.893 --> 00:26:40.090
My name is Elle Woods, Boston by way of Bel Air.

510
00:26:40.163 --> 00:26:41.926
And as my surname would suggest...

511
00:26:41.998 --> 00:26:44.626
I am a passionate advocate for everything in nature...

512
00:26:44.701 --> 00:26:45.861
and a contented citizen...

513
00:26:45.935 --> 00:26:48.495
until my shorthaired Chihuahua, Bruiser...

514
00:26:48.571 --> 00:26:51.768
brought me face-to-face with the animal testing issue.

515
00:26:51.841 --> 00:26:53.240
You're out of order, Miss Woods.

516
00:26:53.309 --> 00:26:55.539
This is a fuel efficiency hearing.

517
00:26:55.612 --> 00:26:58.274
I don't see anything in the agenda about animal testing.

518
00:26:58.348 --> 00:26:59.474
Will you yield the floor?

519
00:26:59.549 --> 00:27:01.073
Absolutely. I'm almost done.

520
00:27:01.151 --> 00:27:03.676
So, in conclusion, I just want to say...

521
00:27:03.753 --> 00:27:05.084
that I am so excited about the day...

522
00:27:05.155 --> 00:27:07.282
that I get to march up those grand Capitol steps...

523
00:27:07.357 --> 00:27:11.020
and drop that very bill in the...

524
00:27:11.094 --> 00:27:12.721
What's it called?

525
00:27:12.796 --> 00:27:15.765
It's like a shiny, mahogany box thing?

